\fR\f(CI\*(C`lm\*(C'\fR\fI\fR
.IX Subsection "lm"
.PP
\fIBug fixes\fR
.IX Subsection "Bug fixes"
.PP
\&\fBMemory leak on the zero\-degrees\-of\-freedom error path.\fR When
\&\f(CW\*(C`valid_n <= p\*(C'\fR, the cleanup freed the \f(CW\*(C`valid_row_names\*(C'\fR \fIarray\fR but not the
per\-row name strings it held (those had been transferred out of \f(CW\*(C`row_names\*(C'\fR,
whose own array was already freed). The strings leaked on every such error.
Added the per\-entry \f(CW\*(C`Safefree\*(C'\fR loop before freeing the array, matching the
normal path.
.PP
\&\fBHoH input validated only the first row.\fR Only the first hash value was
checked to be a \f(CW\*(C`HASHREF\*(C'\fR; subsequent values were \f(CW\*(C`SvRV\*(C'\fR\*(Aqd unconditionally, so
a malformed row (\f(CW\*(C`{ a => {...}, b => 5 }\*(C'\fR) dereferenced a non\-reference. Every
row is now validated, with the partial allocations cleaned up before the
\&\f(CW\*(C`croak\*(C'\fR, mirroring the existing AoH path.
.PP
\&\fR\f(CB\*(C`isspace\*(C'\fR\fB on a possibly\-signed \fR\f(CB\*(C`char\*(C'\fR\fB.\fR \f(CWisspace(*src)\fR is undefined for
byte values Ōēź 0x80 on platforms where \f(CW\*(C`char\*(C'\fR is signed. Cast to
\&\f(CW\*(C`(unsigned char)\*(C'\fR before the call.
.PP
\fISpeed / RAM improvements\fR
.IX Subsection "Speed / RAM improvements"
.PP
\&\fBFormula buffer is now heap\-allocated to fit.\fR \f(CW\*(C`char f_cpy[512]\*(C'\fR silently
truncated any longer formula. Replaced with a buffer sized to
\&\f(CW\*(C`strlen(formula) + 1\*(C'\fR, so there is no fixed limit and no truncation.
.PP
\&\fR\f(CB\*(C`.\*(C'\fR\fB\-expansion buffer is now a growable heap buffer.\fR \f(CW\*(C`char rhs_expanded[2048]\*(C'\fR
silently dropped expanded terms once full. It is now a buffer that doubles on
demand. Appends also went from \f(CW\*(C`strcat\*(C'\fR (which rescans from the start every
time ŌĆö O(n┬▓) over many columns) to an O(1) amortised append that tracks the
write position.
.PP
\&\fBNo more per\-row scratch allocation in matrix construction.\fR The original
\&\f(CW\*(C`safemalloc\*(C'\fR\*(Aqd a \f(CW\*(C`row_x\*(C'\fR buffer, filled it, copied it into \f(CW\*(C`X\*(C'\fR, and freed it
\&\fIfor every row\fR ŌĆö \f(CW\*(C`n\*(C'\fR allocations plus \f(CW\*(C`n*p\*(C'\fR copies. Each candidate row is now
written straight into \f(CW\*(C`X\*(C'\fR at its prospective commit slot; a row that fails
listwise deletion is simply overwritten by the next candidate. This removes the
\&\f(CW\*(C`n\*(C'\fR allocate/free cycles and the copy loop entirely.
.PP
\&\fBCategorical levels sorted with \fR\f(CB\*(C`qsort\*(C'\fR\fB.\fR The level list used an O(n┬▓) bubble
sort; replaced with \f(CW\*(C`qsort\*(C'\fR (relevant only for high\-cardinality factors).
.PP
\&\fBUnused tail of \fR\f(CB\*(C`X\*(C'\fR\fB reclaimed after listwise deletion.\fR \f(CW\*(C`X\*(C'\fR is allocated for
all \f(CW\*(C`n\*(C'\fR rows up front (\f(CW\*(C`valid_n\*(C'\fR is unknown until rows are scanned). When rows
are dropped, \f(CW\*(C`X\*(C'\fR is now \f(CW\*(C`Renew\*(C'\fRed down to \f(CW\*(C`valid_n * p\*(C'\fR, returning the unused
tail to the allocator before the OLS phase.
.PP
\&\fBMinor robustness.\fR The argument\-parsing index was widened from
\&\f(CW\*(C`unsigned short\*(C'\fR to \f(CW\*(C`I32\*(C'\fR to match \f(CW\*(C`items\*(C'\fR, and the HoH row count now uses
\&\f(CW\*(C`HvUSEDKEYS\*(C'\fR rather than relying on \f(CW\*(C`hv_iterinit\*(C'\fR\*(Aqs return value.
.PP
\fIKnown limitations (left unchanged)\fR
.IX Subsection "Known limitations (left unchanged)"
.IP \(bu 4
A multi\-way term such as \f(CW\*(C`a*b*c\*(C'\fR is split only on the first \f(CW\*(C`*\*(C'\fR, so it yields
\&\f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`b*c\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`a:b*c\*(C'\fR rather than a full three\-way expansion. Deeper
interactions silently fail (the unparsable term evaluates to \f(CW\*(C`NaN\*(C'\fR and the
rows are dropped). This matches the documented two\-way \f(CW\*(C`*\*(C'\fR support.
.IP \(bu 4
HoA input takes the row count from the first column; columns shorter than
that simply contribute dropped rows rather than raising an error.
.PP
\fR\f(CI\*(C`oneway_test\*(C'\fR\fI\fR
.IX Subsection "oneway_test"
.PP
Bug fixes
.IX Subsection "Bug fixes"
.PP
\&\fBMemory leaks on error paths.\fR Nearly every \f(CW\*(C`croak\*(C'\fR after an allocation
leaked memory. \f(CW\*(C`croak\*(C'\fR does a \f(CW\*(C`longjmp\*(C'\fR, so anything allocated but not yet
freed is lost. Affected paths:
.IP \(bu 4
AoA and hash first\-pass errors leaked \f(CW\*(C`sizes\*(C'\fR and any \f(CW\*(C`gnames[]\*(C'\fR entries
allocated so far.
.IP \(bu 4
Formula\-mode "not found as an array ref" errors leaked \f(CW\*(C`lhs\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`rhs\*(C'\fR.
.PP
All post\-allocation errors now route through a single \f(CW\*(C`fail:\*(C'\fR label that frees
every pointer unconditionally. Pointers are initialised to \f(CW\*(C`NULL\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`gnames\*(C'\fR
is zero\-allocated with \f(CW\*(C`Newxz\*(C'\fR, so the cleanup is always safe to run.
.PP
\&\fBUndefined and non\-numeric cells silently coerced to \fR\f(CB0.0\fR\fB.\fR The original
second pass used \f(CW\*(C`(svp && *svp) ? SvNV(*svp) : 0.0\*(C'\fR, meaning an \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR or
non\-numeric cell was quietly treated as zero, silently corrupting the
F\-statistic. Each cell is now validated with \f(CW\*(C`SvOK\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`looks_like_number\*(C'\fR;
the call dies naming the group and observation index, consistent with the rest
of \f(CW\*(C`Stats::LikeR\*(C'\fR (\f(CW\*(C`mean\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`sum\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`cor\*(C'\fR, etc.).
.PP
\&\fBUnsigned wraparound on empty array input.\fR \f(CW\*(C`k = (size_t)av_len(in_av) + 1\*(C'\fR
cast to \f(CW\*(C`size_t\*(C'\fR \fIbefore\fR adding, so an empty array (\f(CW\*(C`av_len\*(C'\fR returns \f(CW\-1\fR)
produced \f(CW\*(C`SIZE_MAX\*(C'\fR rather than \f(CW0\fR. Changed to
\&\f(CW\*(C`k = (size_t)(av_len(in_av) + 1)\*(C'\fR so the \f(CW+1\fR is done in signed arithmetic
before the cast.
.PP
\&\fBUnreliable group count from \fR\f(CB\*(C`hv_iterinit\*(C'\fR\fB.\fR \f(CW\*(C`hv_iterinit\*(C'\fR returns the
number of buckets in use rather than the number of keys for tied hashes.
Replaced with \f(CW\*(C`HvUSEDKEYS\*(C'\fR, which always returns the correct key count.
.PP
Improvements
.IX Subsection "Improvements"
.PP
\&\fR\f(CB\*(C`var.equal\*(C'\fR\fB accepted as an alias for \fR\f(CB\*(C`var_equal\*(C'\fR\fB.\fR R users write
\&\f(CW\*(C`var.equal\*(C'\fR; the argument parser now accepts both spellings.
.PP
\&\fBPerl memory API used throughout.\fR \f(CW\*(C`safemalloc\*(C'\fR and manual \f(CW\*(C`memcpy\*(C'\fR replaced
with \f(CW\*(C`Newx\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`Newxz\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`savepv\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`savepvn\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`savepvn\*(C'\fR additionally
preserves embedded NUL bytes in group key strings, which the previous
\&\f(CW\*(C`strlen\*(C'\fR\-based copies silently truncated.
.PP
Known limitations (not changed)
.IX Subsection "Known limitations (not changed)"
.IP \(bu 4
A factor column named \f(CW\*(C`Residuals\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`group_stats\*(C'\fR in a formula call will
collide with reserved top\-level keys in the result hash.
.IP \(bu 4
Group names containing an embedded NUL are stored correctly but are still
truncated at \f(CW\*(C`strlen\*(C'\fR when written into the output hash keys.
.PP
\fR\f(CI\*(C`view\*(C'\fR\fI\fR
.IX Subsection "view"
.PP
default view shifted to 80 characters to match Linux window length
.PP
New features
.IX Subsection "New features"
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fR\f(CB\*(C`rows\*(C'\fR\fB is accepted as a synonym for \fR\f(CB\*(C`n\*(C'\fR\fB\fR (the number of rows shown).
Passing both \f(CW\*(C`n\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`rows\*(C'\fR is an error.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBUnknown arguments are now rejected.\fR \f(CW\*(C`view\*(C'\fR validates its argument names
against the documented set (\f(CW\*(C`n\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`rows\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`na\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`max_width\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`ellipsis\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`gap\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`cols\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`columns\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`to\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`return_only\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`row.names\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`row_names\*(C'\fR) and
dies listing any it does not recognise, so a misspelt option (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`widht\*(C'\fR)
is caught instead of silently ignored.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fR\f(CB\*(C`n\*(C'\fR\fB / \fR\f(CB\*(C`rows\*(C'\fR\fB is validated.\fR It must be a non\-negative integer; \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR or
a non\-numeric value now dies with a clear message instead of producing
warnings and being treated as \f(CW0\fR.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBflat/simple hashes are accepted as input\fR
.PP
Bug fixes
.IX Subsection "Bug fixes"
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fR\f(CB\*(C`n => 0\*(C'\fR\fB now still prints the column header.\fR Column names were collected
only from the rows being shown, so requesting zero rows produced an empty
header line. At least one row is now scanned (when data exists) so the
header always lists the columns.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBAn empty hash (\fR\f(CB\*(C`{}\*(C'\fR\fB) no longer dies.\fR It was rejected as
\&\fI"neither ARRAY nor HASH"\fR; it is now shown as an empty table
(\f(CW\*(C`0 rows x 0 cols\*(C'\fR), matching the handling of an empty array.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBThe \fR\f(CB\*(C`row_names\*(C'\fR\fB alias now drives the Hash\-of\-Hashes label header.\fR The
header for the row\-label column consulted only \f(CW\*(C`row.names\*(C'\fR, so
\&\f(CW\*(C`row_names => \*(Aqid\*(Aq\*(C'\fR displayed \f(CW\*(C`row_name\*(C'\fR instead of \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR. Both spellings are
now honoured consistently.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBMalformed nested values degrade gracefully.\fR A Hash\-of\-Arrays column or
Hash\-of\-Hashes row whose value is not actually an array/hash reference now
renders as empty cells rather than throwing a dereference error.
.PP
Performance
.IX Subsection "Performance"
.IP \(bu 4
Column gathering no longer sorts once per scanned row. Unique column names
are collected across the scanned rows and sorted a single time (same output
order), and the ellipsis length is computed once rather than per cell.
.PP
Tests
.IX Subsection "Tests"
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`t/view.t\*(C'\fR is self\-contained (the \f(CW\*(C`view\*(C'\fR implementation is inlined; it loads
no other files) and covers the new argument handling, the bug fixes above,
and the existing AoH / HoA / HoH behaviour, alignment, truncation, and
output\-path handling.
.PP
\fR\f(CI\*(C`wilcox_test\*(C'\fR\fI\fR
.IX Subsection "wilcox_test"
.PP
Corrected four bugs in the \f(CW\*(C`wilcox_test\*(C'\fR XSUB plus a portability fix in its exact signed\-rank helper. Behaviour on valid input is unchanged: the R\-agreement cases (unpaired \f(CW\*(C`W = 58\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`p = 0.13292\*(C'\fR; paired one\-sided \f(CW\*(C`V = 40\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`p = 0.019531\*(C'\fR; separated exact \f(CW\*(C`W = 0\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`p = 0.028571\*(C'\fR) all still match R\*(Aqs \f(CW\*(C`wilcox.test\*(C'\fR.
.PP
Bug fixes
.IX Subsection "Bug fixes"
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBInvalid \fR\f(CB\*(C`alternative\*(C'\fR\fB is now rejected.\fR Any value other than \f(CW\*(C`less\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`greater\*(C'\fR previously fell through to the two\-sided branch and returned a two\-sided result mislabelled with the bad string, so a typo like \f(CW\*(C`alternative => "twosided"\*(C'\fR silently "worked". It now croaks unless \f(CW\*(C`alternative\*(C'\fR is one of \f(CW\*(C`two.sided\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`less\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`greater\*(C'\fR.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBZero/negative variance is guarded.\fR When every observation is tied the approximation\*(Aqs variance collapses to 0 and the old code divided by \f(CWsqrt(0)\fR: \f(CW\*(C`wilcox_test([5,5,5], [5,5,5])\*(C'\fR returned \f(CW\*(C`p = 0\*(C'\fR (a "significant" difference between identical samples). It now warns and returns \f(CW\*(C`p = 1\*(C'\fR.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBTwo\-sided continuity correction at \fR\f(CB\*(C`z = 0\*(C'\fR\fB.\fR R uses \f(CW\*(C`sign(z) * 0.5\*(C'\fR, so the correction is \f(CW0\fR when the statistic sits exactly on its mean; the old code used \f(CW\-0.5\fR. Example: \f(CW\*(C`wilcox_test([1,4], [2,3], exact => 0)\*(C'\fR changed from \f(CW\*(C`p = 0.698535\*(C'\fR to \f(CW\*(C`p = 1\*(C'\fR (matches R).
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fR\f(CB\*(C`exp\*(C'\fR\fB no longer shadows libm.\fR The local \f(CW\*(C`exp\*(C'\fR accumulator (mean of the statistic) shadowed the C library \f(CWexp()\fR; renamed to \f(CW\*(C`mean_w\*(C'\fR (two\-sample) and \f(CW\*(C`mean_v\*(C'\fR (signed\-rank). No active miscompute, removed as a latent hazard.
.PP
Cosmetic
.IX Subsection "Cosmetic"
.IP \(bu 4
Collapsed a no\-op ternary that assigned the same signed\-rank exact method string on both branches; the \f(CW\*(C`method\*(C'\fR field is now simply \f(CW\*(C`Wilcoxon signed rank exact test\*(C'\fR.
.PP
Portability (exact signed\-rank helper)
.IX Subsection "Portability (exact signed-rank helper)"
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fR\f(CB\*(C`exact_psignrank\*(C'\fR\fB no longer calls \fR\f(CBpowl()\fR\fB.\fR The \f(CW\*(C`2^n\*(C'\fR normaliser is now built by exact repeated doubling, which has no long\-double libm dependency. This fixes an \f(CW\*(C`Undefined symbol "powl"\*(C'\fR load failure reported by a CPAN smoker (FreeBSD, perl 5.20, \f(CW\*(C`nvtype=double\*(C'\fR) whose libm lacks the long\-double math functions; the symbol resolved on glibc, which is why local builds passed. \f(CW\*(C`long double\*(C'\fR accumulation in the DP is retained ŌĆö only the \f(CW\*(C`powl\*(C'\fR call was at fault.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fR\f(CB\*(C`int\*(C'\fR\fB ŌåÆ \fR\f(CB\*(C`size_t\*(C'\fR\fB\fR for \f(CW\*(C`n\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`max_v\*(C'\fR, and the DP loop counters, which also removes a \f(CW\*(C`size_t\*(C'\fR\-to\-\f(CW\*(C`int\*(C'\fR narrowing at the call site. The \f(CWfloor()\fR result (\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR) stays signed so its negative\-\f(CW\*(C`q\*(C'\fR sentinel still fires, and is cast to \f(CW\*(C`size_t\*(C'\fR only after the \f(CW\*(C`k < 0\*(C'\fR check.
.PP
Tests
.IX Subsection "Tests"
.IP \(bu 4
Added \f(CW\*(C`t/wilcox_test.t\*(C'\fR (flat, no subtests): R\-agreement cases, option handling (\f(CW\*(C`paired\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`correct\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`exact\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`mu\*(C'\fR, named/positional \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`y\*(C'\fR, NA dropping), regressions for all four bug fixes, argument\-error and \f(CW\*(C`alternative\*(C'\fR\-validation checks, output shape, and \f(CW\*(C`no_leaks_ok\*(C'\fR coverage of the two\-sample, exact, and paired allocation paths.
